!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <title>Loop Demo</title>
</head> <body> <h2>Print 1 to 10 Using Loops</h2><button onclick="printUsingFor()">Print Using For Loop</button>
<button onclick="printUsingWhile()">Print Using While Loop</button>
<button onclick="printUsingDoWhile()">Print Using Do-While Loop</button>
<h3>Output:</h3>
<p id="output"></p>
<script>
function printUsingFor() {
let result = "For Loop: ";
for (let i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
result += i + " ";
}
document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = result;
}
function printUsingWhile() {
let i = 1;
let result = "While Loop: ";
while (i <= 10) {
result += i + " ";
i++;
}
document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = result;
}
function printUsingDoWhile() {
let i = 1;
let result = "Do-While Loop: ";
do {
result += i + " ";
i++;
} while (i <= 10);document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = result;
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
Output:
8 d) Write a program to print data in object using for-in, for-each and for-of loops.Aim : program to print data in object using for-in, for-each and for-of loops.
Description : This program illustrates the use of for-in, for-each and for-of loops by
printing data in objects.
1.for...in loop  Used to iterate over object properties (keys).
Syntax:
for (key in object) {
// code using object[key]
}
2.for...of loop  Used to iterate over iterables like arrays, strings, etc.
Syntax:
for (element of iterable) {
// code using element
}
3. forEach()  forEach() is an array method in JavaScript.
Syntax:
array.forEach(function(currentValue, index, array)
{
// code to be executed for each element
});
Program:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Looping Through Data</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Looping Through Object and Array</h2>
<button onclick="printData()">Display Data</button>
<p id="forInLoop"></p><p id="forEachLoop"></p> <p id="forOfLoop"></p> <script> function printData() { // Object example let person = { name: "John", age: 25, city: "New York" }; // 1. Using for-in loop (for objects) let forInResult = " "; for (let key in person) { forInResult += key + "=" + person[key] + " ";
} document.getElementById("forInLoop").innerText= "For-In Loop (Object):" +
forInResult; // Array example let fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Mango"]; // 2. Using forEach loop (for arrays) let forEachResult = " "; fruits.forEach(function(fruit, index) { forEachResult += fruit + " ";
});
document.getElementById("forEachLoop").innerText="forEach Loop (Array): " + forEachResult;
// 3. Using for-of loop (for arrays) let forOfResult = " "; for (let fruit of fruits) { forOfResult += fruit + " ";
} document.getElementById("forOfLoop").innerText = "For-Of Loop (Array):" +
forOfResult; </body>
} </script>
